K_Mean 3 Clustering

result <- kclus(
  Radiant1_Var_Null_Trans_Birth_Marital_marketing_campaign, 
  vars = c(
    "Income", "Kidhome", "Teenhome", "NumDealsPurchases", 
    "NumWebPurchases", "NumCatalogPurchases", "NumStorePurchases", 
    "TotalSpend", "TotalAcceptedCmp", "RL_Status_1_5", "Edu"
  ), 
  distance = "euclidean", 
  nr_clus = 3, 
  data_filter = "Income<153924 & MntWines<1324 & MntFruits<147 & MntMeatProducts<842 & MntFishProducts<202 & MntSweetProducts <151 & MntGoldProds<199 & NumDealsPurchases <9 & NumWebPurchases <23 & NumCatalogPurchases<22 & NumWebVisitsMonth <13"
)
summary(result, dec = 2)
